sec.p:
Let the observed data be collected in a matrix X=[x1,…,xp] (N×p) and a matrix Y=[y1,…,yq] (N×q). Here, N denotes the number of subjects, and p and q denote the number of variables in X and Y, respectively. The O2PLS method decomposes X and Y in two joint, specific and residual parts. The dimension of the joint part is given by n, the dimension of each specific part is given by nX and nY, respectively. The joint parts consist of matrices T, U (both N×n), W (p×n) and C (q×n). The matrices T and U are referred to as joint scores or joint latent components, and the matrices W and C are referred to as joint loadings or joint principal components. These joint parts represent the statistical overlap between X and Y. The specific parts consist of matrices TY⊥ (N×nX), UX⊥ (N×nY), PY⊥ (p×nX) and PX⊥ (q×nY). These matrices are referred to as specific scores and loadings, respectively. The residual parts are denoted by E (N×p) and F (N×q). Then, the O2PLS decomposition is 
