Cross-validating. Cross-validation is a well-known technique to choose tuning parameters of a model, while limiting the risk to overfit. All samples are partitioned in k blocks (denoted as folds), and the model is fitted on k−1 folds. The left out fold is used to evaluate the model fit. For O2PLS, an approach to determine the number of components is to maximize the prediction error over a three-dimensional grid of possible integers and select the triple (n,nX,nY) that minimizes this error. As O2PLS is symmetric in X and Y, the sum of the two prediction errors \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
